annotations: The iQOO 12 Pro, also known as the vivo iQOO 12 Pro, is a high-end smartphone with impressive features. It boasts a large 6.78-inch AMOLED display with a resolution of 1440 x 3200 pixels and a 144Hz refresh rate. Powered by the Qualcomm SM8650-AB Snapdragon 8 Gen 3 chipset and 16GB of RAM, this phone offers smooth performance. The device comes with a triple main camera setup, including a 50MP wide, 64MP periscope telephoto, and 50MP ultrawide lens, capable of recording 8K videos. It also features a 16MP selfie camera. The phone is equipped with a 5100mAh Li-Po battery and supports 120W wired, 50W wireless, and 10W reverse wireless charging. Additionally, it offers IP68 dust/water resistance and comes in black, red, and white colors. With its premium build and top-notch specifications, the iQOO 12 Pro is a compelling option for smartphone enthusiasts.

The Emporia Elegance is a compact and lightweight mobile phone with a classic design. It features a 1.8-inch TFT display with a resolution of 128 x 160 pixels, a 2MB RAM, and a 1100mAh Li-Ion battery. The phone supports GSM network and has a Mini-SIM slot. It also comes with a built-in flashlight and FM radio. The phone, which was announced in 2012, is available in black, white, and brown colors. With its simple features and long battery standby time of up to 300 hours, the Emporia Elegance is a reliable and practical choice for basic communication needs.

The XOLO Era is a smartphone that was announced in July 2015 and has since been discontinued. It features a 5.0-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 480 x 854 pixels. The phone is powered by a quad-core 1.2 GHz Spreadtrum 7731 chipset and comes with 1GB of RAM and 8GB of internal storage, which can be expanded via a microSDHC card slot. The main camera has 8MP resolution and features LED flash, panorama, and HDR, while the selfie camera has 2MP resolution. The phone runs on Android 4.4.2 (KitKat) and is equipped with a 2100mAh removable Li-Ion battery. Other features include Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 2.1, GPS, FM radio, and microUSB 2.0. The XOLO Era is available in black and was priced at around 60 EUR.

The NEC e636 is a compact and lightweight mobile phone with a 2.2-inch TFT display and a second external mono OLED display. It features a 2MP main camera with video recording capability and a CIF videocall camera for selfies. The phone has a miniSD card slot for memory expansion and comes with 32MB of internal storage. It supports GSM and UMTS networks with 2G and 3G bands and offers Bluetooth connectivity. The removable Li-Ion 900mAh battery provides up to 270 hours of standby time and up to 4 hours of talk time. The phone, announced in February 2006, comes in a sleek black color and is equipped with features like SMS, MMS, email, and downloadable games. With its compact design and essential features, the NEC e636 offers a practical and reliable mobile communication experience.

The Sony Xperia 10 V is a sleek and modern smartphone with a 6.1-inch OLED display and a resolution of 1080 x 2520 pixels. It runs on Android 13, upgradeable to Android 14, and is powered by the Qualcomm SM6375 Snapdragon 695 5G chipset. The phone comes with either 6GB or 8GB of RAM and 128GB of internal storage, which is expandable via microSDXC. The main camera features a triple setup with 48MP, 8MP telephoto, and 8MP ultrawide lenses, while the selfie camera has an 8MP sensor. The device also boasts a 5000mAh non-removable battery with wired PD and QC charging. Additionally, it includes features such as a side-mounted fingerprint sensor, IP65/IP68 dust/water resistance, and stereo speakers. The Sony Xperia 10 V is available in black, white, sage green, and lavender, and is priced at €274.55 / $349.99 / £269.99.

The Plum Ram 8 is a rugged feature phone with a compact design, measuring 111.5 x 57.5 x 22 mm and weighing 134g. It features a 2.4-inch TFT display with a resolution of 240 x 320 pixels and is powered by a Mediatek MT6276A chipset. The phone comes with 128MB of internal storage and 64MB of RAM, expandable via microSDHC. It sports a 5MP main camera with LED flash and can record videos at 240p@15fps. The device is equipped with a 1200mAh removable battery, providing up to 120 hours of standby time and 8 hours of talk time on 3G. Other features include dual SIM support, IP68 dust/water resistance, FM radio, and a 3.5mm headphone jack. The Plum Ram 8 is available in black and black/orange color options.

The Amazon Fire HD 8 Plus (2022) is a compact and lightweight tablet with a sleek design, featuring an 8.0-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 800 x 1280 pixels. It runs on Android 11, Fire OS 8, powered by a Mediatek MT8169A chipset and a Hexa-core CPU. The tablet comes with 3GB of RAM and is available in 32GB or 64GB internal storage options, expandable via a dedicated microSDXC slot. The main camera has a 5MP sensor and can record 1080p videos, while the selfie camera has a 2MP sensor with 720p video recording capability. The device supports Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac, Bluetooth 5.2, and has a USB Type-C 2.0 port for charging and data transfer. It also features a 3.5mm headphone jack and stereo speakers for audio. The tablet is available in a stylish gray color and is priced at around 120 EUR.

The Ulefone Armor X12 Pro is a rugged smartphone designed for durability and outdoor use. It features a 5.45-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 720 x 1440 pixels and is powered by the Android 13 operating system. The phone is equipped with a MediaTek Helio G36 chipset, 4GB of RAM, and 64GB of internal storage, which can be expanded via a microSDXC card slot. The main camera has a 13MP sensor with LED flash and can record 1080p videos, while the front-facing camera has an 8MP sensor. The device is IP68/IP69K dust and water-resistant and has a MIL-STD-810H compliant build, making it suitable for harsh environments. It is powered by a 4860mAh non-removable battery and supports 10W wired charging. The Ulefone Armor X12 Pro also features NFC, a 3.5mm headphone jack, and a USB Type-C 2.0 port. It comes in three color options: Black, Black/Orange, and Black/Green, and is priced at €118.99 / $104.99 / £139.99.

The Sony Ericsson Live with Walkman, also known as the Live with Walkman, is a smartphone that was announced in August 2011 and released in October 2011. It features a 3.2-inch TFT display with a resolution of 320 x 480 pixels and is powered by a 1.0 GHz Qualcomm Snapdragon S2 processor. The phone runs on Android 2.3 (Gingerbread) and comes with 512MB of RAM and 320MB of internal storage, which can be expanded using a microSDHC card. The main camera has a 5MP sensor with LED flash and can record videos at 720p resolution, while the front-facing camera is VGA. The device is equipped with a removable 1200mAh Li-Ion battery that provides up to 14 hours of talk time on 2G and up to 6 hours and 42 minutes on 3G. Other features include Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, GPS, FM radio, and a 3.5mm headphone jack. The phone is available in black and white colors and was priced at around 120 EUR.

The Ericsson T20e, announced in 2001 and now discontinued, is a GSM mobile phone with dimensions of 101 x 54 x 28 mm and a weight of 128 g. It features a monochrome graphic display with a resolution of 101 x 33 pixels and 3 x 12 chars. The phone has no card slot for memory expansion and comes with a removable NiMH battery providing a standby time of 200 hours and talk time of 10 hours. It is available in 5 colors - Purple Wild, Blue Whirl, Lime Twist, Silver Weave, and Beige Harmony. The phone also offers basic features such as SMS messaging, WAP browser, alarm, and 5 pre-installed games.

Introducing the Lava Blaze 2, a sleek and stylish smartphone with a 6.5-inch IPS LCD display and a resolution of 720 x 1600 pixels. Powered by Android 12 and the Unisoc Tiger T616 chipset, this phone comes with 6GB of RAM and 128GB of internal storage, expandable via microSDXC. The dual main camera features a 13MP wide lens and a 2MP sensor, while the selfie camera boasts 8MP. With a 5000mAh Li-Po battery and 18W wired charging, the Lava Blaze 2 is available in Glass Blue, Glass Black, and Glass Orange colors, offering a range of features including a side-mounted fingerprint sensor, FM radio, and USB Type-C 2.0 connectivity. This device is a versatile and affordable option for those in search of a reliable smartphone.

The Unnecto Quattro S is a compact and lightweight smartphone with a 4.0-inch TFT display and a resolution of 480 x 800 pixels. It runs on Android 5.1 (Lollipop) and is powered by a quad-core 1.2 GHz CPU with 1GB of RAM and 8GB of internal storage, expandable via microSD. The main camera has a 5MP sensor with features like LED flash, HDR, and panorama, capable of recording 720p videos, while the front camera has a 1.3MP sensor. The phone supports dual SIM cards and has a removable 1400mAh Li-Ion battery. It also features Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, GPS, stereo FM radio, and microUSB 2.0 connectivity options. The Unnecto Quattro S comes in black, white, and navy color options and was announced in May 2016, with a subsequent release in July of the same year.

Introducing the Ulefone Armor X12, a rugged smartphone designed for durability and performance. With its IP68/IP69K dust/water resistant certification and MIL-STD-810H compliance, this phone is built to withstand tough conditions. The 5.45-inch IPS LCD display offers a clear viewing experience, while the 13MP main camera and 8MP selfie camera allow you to capture moments on the go. Powered by Android 13 (Go edition) and equipped with a Mediatek MT6761V/WAB Helio A22 chipset, this phone ensures smooth operation. The 4860mAh battery provides long-lasting power, and the device also features 3GB of RAM and 32GB of internal storage. With Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, NFC, and GPS capabilities, the Ulefone Armor X12 offers a range of connectivity options. Available in black, black/orange, and black/green, this smartphone combines ruggedness with functionality for users in various environments.

The T-Mobile REVVL 6 Pro, also known as the REVVL 6 Pro, is a smartphone with a 6.82-inch IPS LCD display and a resolution of 720 x 1640 pixels. It runs on Android 12 and is powered by the Mediatek MT6833 Dimensity 700 chipset with 6GB of RAM and 128GB of internal storage. The phone features a quad-camera setup with a 50MP main camera and a 16MP selfie camera. It is equipped with a side-mounted fingerprint sensor, a 5000mAh non-removable battery with 15W wired and wireless charging, and comes in the color Dark Shadow. The T-Mobile REVVL 6 Pro supports 5G connectivity and has a splash-resistant body design. With its neutral and balanced features, the REVVL 6 Pro is a versatile and reliable smartphone option.

The Infinix Note 30i is a versatile smartphone with a 6.66" AMOLED display and a resolution of 1080x2400 pixels, offering a clear and vibrant viewing experience. It features a powerful 64MP dual main camera with Quad-LED flash and a 16MP selfie camera with Dual-LED flash, allowing users to capture high-quality photos and videos. With 8GB of RAM and 256GB of internal storage, this device provides ample space for storing media and running multiple apps simultaneously. The phone is powered by a Mediatek MT6769 Helio G85 chipset and a Li-Po 5000mAh battery, ensuring smooth performance and long-lasting battery life. Additionally, it comes with IP53 dust and splash resistance, dual speakers with JBL sound, and a side-mounted fingerprint sensor for added security. The Infinix Note 30i is available in Variable Gold, Obsidian Black, and Impression Green colors, catering to different style preferences.

The Parla Sonic 3.5S is a compact and lightweight smartphone with a 3.5-inch TFT display and a resolution of 320x480 pixels. It runs on Android 4.4 (KitKat) and is powered by a Spreadtrum 7715 chipset with a 1.0 GHz Cortex-A7 CPU and Mali-400 GPU. The phone has 256MB RAM and 512MB of internal storage, which can be expanded via a microSDHC card slot. It features a 2MP main camera with LED flash and HDR, capable of recording 480p videos, and a removable 1300mAh Li-Ion battery. The device supports dual SIM cards and offers Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, A-GPS, and stereo FM radio connectivity options. With its simple design and basic features, the Parla Sonic 3.5S is a budget-friendly option for users looking for a no-frills smartphone.

The Orange Sydney, also known as Sydney, was announced in 2011 and released in the same year. It features a 3.2-inch TFT resistive touchscreen with a resolution of 240 x 400 pixels. The phone is equipped with a 3.15 MP main camera and supports video recording. It has a microSD card slot for expandable storage and runs on a removable Li-Ion battery with up to 312 hours of standby time and 6 hours of talk time. The phone supports GSM network technology, GPRS, and EDGE, and also features Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, and FM radio. The Orange Sydney comes in black and white color options and is designed with a mini-SIM card slot. It is a discontinued model with a simple and functional design, suitable for basic communication and multimedia needs.

The Alcatel 1V (2021) is a budget-friendly smartphone with a 6.52-inch IPS LCD display and a resolution of 720 x 1600 pixels. It runs on Android 11 (Go edition) and is powered by the Mediatek MT6761 Helio A22 chipset with 2GB of RAM. The phone comes with a 13MP main camera, along with a 5MP front camera for selfies. It has a non-removable 5000mAh Li-Ion battery and supports 10W wired charging. The device also features a rear-mounted fingerprint sensor, accelerometer, proximity sensor, and compass. With its affordable price point and basic yet functional features, the Alcatel 1V (2021) is a practical choice for those looking for a simple and reliable smartphone.

The HP 7 Plus is a compact and lightweight tablet with a 7.0-inch IPS LCD display, offering a resolution of 600 x 1024 pixels. Powered by a quad-core 1.0 GHz Cortex-A7 processor and 1GB of RAM, it runs on the Android 4.2.2 (Jelly Bean) operating system. The device comes with 8GB of internal storage, expandable via a microSDHC card slot. It features a 2MP main camera and a VGA selfie camera, along with a non-removable Li-Po 2800 mAh battery. The tablet supports Wi-Fi 802.11 b/g/n and Bluetooth connectivity, and is equipped with a microUSB 2.0 port for charging and data transfer. With its sleek silver design and a price of around 70 EUR, the HP 7 Plus offers a budget-friendly option for users in need of a basic and portable tablet.

Introducing the Motorola Razr 40 Ultra, a cutting-edge smartphone with a foldable LTPO AMOLED display, offering a 6.9-inch screen when unfolded and a secondary external display for added convenience. Powered by the Qualcomm SM8475 Snapdragon 8+ Gen 1 chipset and running on Android 13, this device boasts a dual main camera with 12MP and 13MP lenses, as well as a 32MP selfie camera. With options for 8GB or 12GB of RAM and internal storage ranging from 256GB to 512GB, the Razr 40 Ultra also features a 3800mAh Li-Po battery with 30W wired and 5W wireless charging capabilities. Additionally, it supports 5G connectivity and comes with a range of sensors including a side-mounted fingerprint sensor. Available in Infinite Black, Glacier Blue, and Viva Magenta, the Motorola Razr 40 Ultra offers a sleek and versatile mobile experience for users.

The Telit t250 is a GSM mobile phone that was announced in 2006, but unfortunately, it was later cancelled. It features a compact design with dimensions of 96.5 x 49.5 x 15.4 mm and weighs 76g. The phone has a TFT display with 256K colors and a secondary CSTN display with 65K colors. It comes with a basic VGA main camera and no selfie camera. The phone has limited memory with no card slot and only 7MB of internal storage. It also lacks modern features such as Bluetooth, WLAN, and a 3.5mm jack. The removable Li-Ion 800 mAh battery powers the device. Overall, the Telit t250 is a simple and compact phone with basic features, suitable for users looking for a no-frills mobile experience.

Introducing the Lava Yuva Pro, a budget-friendly smartphone with a 6.52-inch IPS LCD display and a resolution of 720 x 1600 pixels. It runs on Android 12 and is powered by a 5000mAh non-removable Li-Po battery. The phone features a triple main camera with a 13MP wide lens and 1080p video recording capability, as well as an 8MP selfie camera. With 3GB of RAM and 32GB of internal storage, expandable via microSDXC, the Yuva Pro offers a decent performance. It also comes with a side-mounted fingerprint sensor, dual SIM capability, and a USB Type-C 2.0 port for charging and OTG support. Available in Metallic Black, Metallic Blue, and Metallic Grey, the Lava Yuva Pro is a practical choice for those looking for a reliable and affordable smartphone.

The Kyocera DuraForce is a durable and rugged smartphone designed for tough environments. It features a 4.5-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 720 x 1280 pixels and is powered by a Qualcomm Snapdragon 400 chipset with 2GB of RAM. The phone comes with 16GB of internal storage, expandable via a microSDHC card slot. It sports an 8MP main camera with features like LED flash, HDR, and panorama, capable of recording 1080p videos, as well as a 2MP front-facing camera. The device runs on Android 4.4.2 (KitKat) and is equipped with a non-removable 3100mAh Li-Ion battery. Additionally, it offers IP68 dust/water resistance and MIL-STD-810G compliance, making it suitable for outdoor and industrial use. The Kyocera DuraForce also supports Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, NFC, GPS, and has a microUSB 2.0 port for charging and data transfer. It is available in black and was announced in November 2014.

The Unnecto Quattro V is a compact and lightweight smartphone with a 4.0-inch IPS LCD display, offering a resolution of 480 x 800 pixels. It runs on the Android 5.1 (Lollipop) operating system and is powered by a quad-core 1.3 GHz Cortex-A7 processor with Mali-400 GPU. The phone comes with 8GB of internal storage and 1GB of RAM, which can be expanded via a microSDHC card slot. The main camera has a 5MP sensor with PDAF, LED flash, HDR, and panorama features, capable of recording 720p videos at 30fps, while the selfie camera has a 1.3MP sensor. The device supports Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 4.0, GPS, and stereo FM radio, and is equipped with a 1600mAh removable Li-Ion battery. Available in black, white, and blue colors, the Unnecto Quattro V offers a simple and functional smartphone experience.

The Amoi WMA8703, also known as WMA8703, is a GSM/UMTS phone that was announced in 2007 and has since been discontinued. It features a compact body with dimensions of 109.4 x 48 x 13.8 mm and a 2.2-inch TFT display with a resolution of 320 x 240 pixels. The phone comes with a 3.15 MP main camera and a VGA videocall camera for selfies. It has a microSD card slot for expandable storage and a 920mAh removable Li-Ion battery. The phone supports messaging, browsing, and gaming, and comes in a sleek black color.

The Alcatel 1SE (2020) is a budget-friendly smartphone with a 6.22" IPS LCD display and a resolution of 720x1520 pixels. It features a triple main camera with 13MP, 5MP, and 2MP lenses, as well as a 5MP selfie camera. The phone runs on Android 10 and is powered by the Unisoc SC9863A chipset with 2-4GB of RAM. It has a 4000mAh Li-Po battery and comes with 32GB, 64GB, or 128GB of internal storage. The device supports GSM, HSPA, and LTE networks and has a hybrid dual SIM slot. Other features include a rear-mounted fingerprint sensor, FM radio, and a 3.5mm headphone jack. The Alcatel 1SE (2020) is available in Agate Green and Power Gray colors and is priced at around 150 EUR.

The Sendo K1, also known as K1, is a mobile phone that was announced in the first quarter of 2005 but was later cancelled. It features a 65K color display with a 5-way navigation key and downloadable wallpapers and animated screensavers. The phone has no expandable memory and no camera. It also lacks a loudspeaker and a 3.5mm jack but supports vibration and downloadable polyphonic ringtones for alerts. The Sendo K1 is equipped with Bluetooth 1.2 for connectivity and has a removable Li-Ion battery with a standby time of up to 400 hours and a talk time of up to 7 hours. The phone comes in a mini-SIM format and is available in unspecified colors.

The NIU Andy 5EI is a discontinued smartphone that was announced in May 2014 and released in July 2014. It features a 5.0-inch TFT display with a resolution of 480 x 854 pixels and is powered by a dual-core 1.0 GHz Cortex-A7 processor with 512MB of RAM. The phone comes with a 5MP main camera with LED flash and a 1.3MP selfie camera. It has a removable Li-Ion 1550 mAh battery and runs on the Android 4.2 (Jelly Bean) operating system. The device supports dual SIM (Mini-SIM/ Micro-SIM) and offers connectivity options such as Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, GPS, and microUSB 2.0. The NIU Andy 5EI is available in black, white, red, blue, and green color options.

The Sharp Aquos V7 Plus is a mid-range smartphone with a 6.74-inch IPS LCD display and a resolution of 720 x 1600 pixels. It runs on Android 13 and is powered by the Mediatek MT6765 Helio G37 chipset. The phone comes with either 4GB or 6GB of RAM and 128GB or 256GB of internal storage, which is expandable via microSDXC. The main camera setup includes a 50MP wide lens, a 2MP macro lens, and a 2MP depth sensor, while the selfie camera is 8MP. The device features a side-mounted fingerprint sensor, a 5010mAh non-removable battery with 18W wired charging, and comes in blue and dark blue colors. With its competitive pricing of around 180 EUR, the Aquos V7 Plus offers a balanced combination of features for everyday use.

Introducing the Google Pixel Fold, a cutting-edge foldable smartphone with a sleek design and advanced features. Boasting a foldable OLED display with a 120Hz refresh rate, HDR10+ support, and a high brightness level of 1000 nits, this device offers a seamless and immersive viewing experience. Equipped with a powerful Google Tensor G2 chipset and 12GB of RAM, the Pixel Fold delivers smooth performance and multitasking capabilities. The device also features a versatile camera system, including a triple main camera setup with a 48MP wide lens and 5x optical zoom, as well as an 8MP selfie camera. With a 4821mAh Li-Po battery, IPX8 water resistance, and 5G connectivity, the Pixel Fold is designed to meet the demands of modern smartphone users. Available in Porcelain and Obsidian colors, this innovative device sets a new standard for foldable smartphones.

The HP 10 Plus is a discontinued tablet that was announced in 2014. It features a 10.1-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 1920 x 1200 pixels. The tablet runs on Android 4.4.2 (KitKat) and is powered by a quad-core 1.0 GHz CPU, coupled with 2GB of RAM and 16GB of internal storage, expandable via a microSDHC card slot. The device is equipped with a 5MP main camera with HDR capabilities and can record videos at 1080p@30fps, while the front-facing camera has a 2MP resolution. It also comes with a non-removable Li-Po 7700 mAh battery, providing up to 6 hours of multimedia talk time. The tablet supports Wi-Fi 802.11 b/g/n, Bluetooth 4.0, GPS, and has a microUSB 2.0 port for charging and data transfer. Additionally, it features stereo speakers, a 3.5mm headphone jack, and sensors such as accelerometer and gyro. The HP 10 Plus is available in Black/Silver color options.

The HP 7 VoiceTab is a discontinued tablet that was announced in October 2014. It features a 6.95-inch TFT display with a resolution of 600 x 1024 pixels and is powered by a quad-core 1.3 GHz Cortex-A7 processor. The tablet comes with 1GB of RAM and 8GB of internal storage, which can be expanded via a microSDHC card slot. It has a 5MP main camera with LED flash and a VGA selfie camera. The device runs on Android 4.4.2 (KitKat) and is equipped with a non-removable 3000mAh Li-Ion battery. The HP 7 VoiceTab also supports Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 4.0, GPS, and has a microUSB 2.0 port for charging and data transfer. It comes in black and white color options and was priced at around 140 EUR.

The Vodafone Smart E9 is a budget-friendly smartphone with a 5.0-inch IPS LCD display and a resolution of 480 x 960 pixels. It runs on Android 8.1 Oreo (Go edition) and is powered by a Mediatek MT6739 chipset with a quad-core 1.5 GHz Cortex-A53 CPU. The phone comes with 1GB of RAM and 8GB of internal storage, expandable via microSD. It features a 5MP main camera with LED flash and a 2MP front camera. The device is equipped with a 2000mAh non-removable battery and supports Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, GPS, and FM radio. The Vodafone Smart E9 is available in the color Anthracite and is priced at around 70 EUR.

The Oppo A2x is a versatile smartphone with a sleek design and a range of impressive features. Boasting a 6.56-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 720 x 1612 pixels, it offers a clear and vibrant viewing experience. Powered by an Android 13 operating system and a Mediatek MT6833V/ZA Dimensity 6020 chipset, this phone ensures smooth performance. With options for 6GB, 8GB, or 12GB of RAM and internal storage ranging from 128GB to 256GB, users have ample space for their apps, photos, and videos. The device is equipped with a dual main camera setup featuring 13MP and 2MP lenses, as well as a 5MP front-facing camera for high-quality selfies. Additionally, the phone includes a 5000mAh Li-Po battery for long-lasting usage. Available in black, gold, and purple, the Oppo A2x offers a stylish and reliable mobile experience at an affordable price point.

The Modu Speedy jacket is a compact and lightweight GSM mobile phone with a 1.3-inch AMOLED display and a resolution of 128x96 pixels. It was announced in 2009 and has since been discontinued. The phone features a removable Li-Po 530 mAh battery, providing up to 100 hours of standby time and up to 2 hours and 30 minutes of talk time. It comes in a stylish red on black color and includes a loudspeaker but no 3.5mm jack for headphones. The phone has a 1.6GB internal memory, supports SMS messaging, and comes with pre-installed games. Additionally, it has a proprietary USB port for charging and data transfer. The Modu Speedy jacket does not have a camera, WLAN, Bluetooth 1.2, or any other sensors. It is a basic and functional mobile phone designed for simple communication and entertainment.

Introducing the BLU G33, a budget-friendly smartphone with a 6.26" IPS LCD display and a resolution of 480x960 pixels. The phone features a 5MP dual main camera with LED flash and 1080p video recording, as well as a 5MP selfie camera. Running on Android 13 (Go edition) and powered by an octa-core 1.6 GHz processor, the G33 comes with 2GB of RAM and 16GB of internal storage, expandable via microSDXC. It supports dual SIM cards and has a 3000mAh removable Li-Ion battery. The phone also includes features such as Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, GPS, FM radio, and a USB Type-C port. Available in black, burgundy, earthy, and green colors, the BLU G33 is priced at around 60 EUR.

The Philips S337 is a dual SIM smartphone that was announced in October 2015 and released in November 2015. It features a 5.0-inch TFT display with a resolution of 480 x 854 pixels and is powered by a quad-core 1.3 GHz processor. The phone comes with 8GB of internal storage and 1GB of RAM, with the option to expand storage using a microSDHC card. The main camera is 5MP with autofocus and LED flash, while the selfie camera is VGA. The phone runs on Android 5.1 (Lollipop) and is equipped with a 2000mAh removable battery. Other features include Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, GPS, FM radio, and microUSB 2.0 connectivity. The Philips S337 is available in black and has a sleek and compact design, measuring 144.8 x 72.5 x 10.4 mm and weighing 152g.

Introducing the Energizer Hard Case G5, a rugged and durable smartphone designed to withstand tough conditions. With a 6.3-inch IPS LCD display and a resolution of 1080 x 2340 pixels, this phone offers a clear and vibrant viewing experience. The main camera features a triple setup with 48 MP, 20 MP, and 13 MP lenses, while the selfie camera boasts 8 MP. Powered by the Android 11 operating system and a Mediatek MT6853 Dimensity 800U chipset, the Hard Case G5 also comes with 128GB of internal storage and 6GB of RAM. Additionally, it is equipped with a 5000mAh non-removable Li-Po battery, ensuring long-lasting power. Other notable features include IP69 dust/water resistance, drop-to-concrete resistance, and NFC capability. Available in black, the Energizer Hard Case G5 is a reliable and versatile option for those in need of a sturdy smartphone.

The Bosch 909 Dual is a GSM mobile phone that was announced in 1999 and has since been discontinued. It features a monochrome graphic display with a resolution of 4 x 16 chars and is equipped with a removable Li-Ion 650 mAh battery that provides a standby time of 70 hours and talk time of 3 hours. The phone has a Mini-SIM card slot and a phonebook capacity of 100 entries, with support for SMS messaging. It also comes in 3 different colors and has a compact body with dimensions of 112 x 50 x 17 mm and a weight of 99 grams. The Bosch 909 Dual does not have a camera, loudspeaker, Bluetooth, or radio, and it does not support GPRS or EDGE technology. Additionally, it does not have a 3.5mm jack or a card slot for memory expansion.

The MWg UBiQUiO 503g, also known as UBiQUiO 503g, is a Windows Mobile 6 Professional smartphone that was announced in April 2007 and released in July 2007. It features a 2.4-inch TFT resistive touchscreen with a resolution of 320 x 240 pixels and is powered by an Intel XScale PXA 270 520 MHz CPU. The phone comes with 96MB RAM and 192MB ROM, expandable via a microSD card slot. It has a 2MP main camera with autofocus and video recording capabilities, as well as a videocall camera for selfies. The device supports GSM and HSPA networks, with Wi-Fi and Bluetooth connectivity options. It is powered by a removable 1500mAh Li-Ion battery, providing up to 250 hours of standby time and up to 4 hours of talk time. The UBiQUiO 503g is available in black and gray color options and is equipped with a QWERTY keyboard for easy typing.

The iPhone 15, announced on September 12, 2023, and released on September 22, 2023, features a 6.1-inch Super Retina XDR OLED display with a resolution of 1179 x 2556 pixels. It is powered by the Apple A16 Bionic chipset and runs on iOS 17. The phone comes with a dual main camera setup, featuring a 48 MP wide lens and a 12 MP ultrawide lens, as well as a 12 MP selfie camera. The device is equipped with a non-removable Li-Ion 3349 mAh battery and supports fast wired and wireless charging.
